Commands	Usage	Purpose
git initi <location>	git init .	to initialise the git repo in our system
git clone <git url>	git clone https://github.com/umaparvat/Ansible	to clone or download the project into our system
git status	git status	to show the status of the project changes
git add -A or git add .	git add .	To add all files to the directory
git add <new file name>	git add ec2instance.yml	To add a particular file into the git directory
git commit -m "<commit messgae>"	git commit -m "added index.html"	To commit changesin the repo but not synced yet to github.com
git push <url>	git push https://github.com/umaparvat/Ansible	This'll be pushed to the repository in github.com. This will work only with github.com
git pull <url>	git pull https://github.com/umaparvat/Ansible	content will be pulled from github.com to our system. This will work only with github.com
git branch	git branch	to see the branches in the git of our system
git branch <branchName>	git branch test	It creates a new branch of all the codes in primary branch(master). In this usage, it creates a new branch test with a copy of all codes of master branch(primary branch)
git checkout <branch name>	git checkout test	to switch to the new branch
git merge <primary branch>	git merge master	To merge with primary branch
git push --set-upstream <branch name>	git push --set-upstream test	To push the content to github
		
